	<section>
		<title>Overview</title>
			<para>The <constant>MIME</constant> class provides facilities for mapping file extensions to
MIME types and vice versa and obtaining human-readable descriptions
from MIME types.</para>
			<para><note>Instances of the <constant>MIME</constant> class are never created; all methods are static.</note></para>
